org.forgerock.openidm.quartz.impl

Interface ScheduledService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ScriptRegistryService, SynchronizationService, SystemObjectSetService, TaskScannerService

    public interface ScheduledService
    OSGi services wanting to be schedulable via the Scheduler service must implement this interface.

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        void execute(org.forgerock.services.context.Context context,
             Map<String,Object> scheduledContext)
      throws ExecutionException
        Invoked by the scheduler when the scheduler triggers.
        Parameters:
        context - the Context to use for the request
        scheduledContext - Context information passed by the scheduler service
        Throws:
        ExecutionException - if execution of the scheduled work failed. Implementations can also throw RuntimeExceptions which will get logged.

      • auditScheduledService

        void auditScheduledService(org.forgerock.services.context.Context context,
                           org.forgerock.audit.events.AuditEvent auditEvent)
                    throws ExecutionException
        Invoked by the scheduler to audit the scheduled event.
        Parameters:
        context - the context to use to audit the event
        auditEvent - the event to audit
        Throws:
        ExecutionException - if the audit event fails
